name: DocumentName
desc: The name of the document from which this image was scanned.

name: PageName
desc: The name of the page from which this image was scanned.

name: XPosition
desc: X position of the image.

name: YPosition
desc: Y position of the image.

name: T4Options
desc: Options for Group 3 Fax compression

name: T6Options
desc: Options for Group 4 Fax compression

name: PageNumber
desc: The page number of the page from which this image was scanned.

name: TransferFunction
desc: Describes a transfer function for the image in tabular style.

name: Predictor
desc: A mathematical operator that is applied to the image data before an encoding scheme is applied.

name: WhitePoint
desc: The chromaticity of the white point of the image.

name: PrimaryChromaticities
desc: The chromaticities of the primaries of the image.

name: HalftoneHints
desc: Conveys to the halftone function the range of gray levels within a colorimetrically-specified image that should retain tonal detail.

name: TileWidth
desc: The tile width in pixels. This is the number of columns in each tile.

name: TileLength
desc: The tile length (height) in pixels. This is the number of rows in each tile.

name: TileOffsets
desc: For each tile, the byte offset of that tile, as compressed and stored on disk.

name: TileByteCounts
desc: For each tile, the number of (compressed) bytes in that tile.

name: BadFaxLines
desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, denotes the number of 'bad' scan lines encountered by the facsimile device.

name: CleanFaxData
desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, indicates if 'bad' lines encountered during reception are stored in the data, or if 'bad' lines have been replaced by the receiver.

name: ConsecutiveBadFaxLines
desc: Used in the TIFF-F standard, denotes the maximum number of consecutive 'bad' scanlines received.

name: SubIFDs
desc: Offset to child IFDs.

name: InkSet
desc: The set of inks used in a separated (PhotometricInterpretation=5) image.

name: InkNames
desc: The name of each ink used in a separated image.

name: NumberOfInks
desc: The number of inks.

name: DotRange
desc: The component values that correspond to a 0% dot and 100% dot.

name: TargetPrinter
desc: A description of the printing environment for which this separation is intended.

name: SampleFormat
desc: Specifies how to interpret each data sample in a pixel.

name: SMinSampleValue
desc: Specifies the minimum sample value.

name: SMaxSampleValue
desc: Specifies the maximum sample value.

name: TransferRange
desc: Expands the range of the TransferFunction.

name: ClipPath
desc: Mirrors the essentials of PostScript's path creation functionality.

name: XClipPathUnits
desc: The number of units that span the width of the image, in terms of integer ClipPath coordinates.

name: YClipPathUnits
desc: The number of units that span the height of the image, in terms of integer ClipPath coordinates.

name: Indexed
desc: Aims to broaden the support for indexed images to include support for any color space.

name: JPEGTables
desc: JPEG quantization and/or Huffman tables.

name: OPIProxy
desc: OPI-related.

name: ProfileType
desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the type of data stored in this file or IFD.

name: FaxProfile
desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the 'profile' that applies to this file.

name: CodingMethods
desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, indicates which coding methods are used in the file.

name: VersionYear
desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the year of the standard specified by the FaxProfile field.

name: ModeNumber
desc: Used in the TIFF-FX standard, denotes the mode of the standard specified by the FaxProfile field.

name: Decode
desc: Used in the TIFF-F and TIFF-FX standards, holds information about the ITULAB (PhotometricInterpretation = 10) encoding.

name: DefaultImageColor
desc: Defined in the Mixed Raster Content part of RFC 2301, is the default color needed in areas where no image is available.

name: JPEGProc
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGInterchangeFormat
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGInterchangeFormatLength
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGRestartInterval
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGLosslessPredictors
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGPointTransforms
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGQTables
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGDCTables
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: JPEGACTables
desc: Old-style JPEG compression field. TechNote2 invalidates this part of the specification.

name: YCbCrCoefficients
desc: The transformation from RGB to YCbCr image data.

name: YCbCrSubSampling
desc: Specifies the subsampling factors used for the chrominance components of a YCbCr image.

name: YCbCrPositioning
desc: Specifies the positioning of subsampled chrominance components relative to luminance samples.

name: ReferenceBlackWhite
desc: Specifies a pair of headroom and footroom image data values (codes) for each pixel component.

name: StripRowCounts
desc: Defined in the Mixed Raster Content part of RFC 2301, used to replace RowsPerStrip for IFDs with variable-sized strips.

name: XMP
desc: XML packet containing XMP metadata

name: ImageID
desc: OPI-related.

name: ImageLayer
desc: Defined in the Mixed Raster Content part of RFC 2301, used to denote the particular function of this Image in the mixed raster scheme.
